1
00:02:24,540 --> 00:02:26,258
Is it true you're a real doctor?

2
00:02:26,460 --> 00:02:27,813
Definitively.

3
00:02:28,100 --> 00:02:29,374
Here's the car.

4
00:02:39,300 --> 00:02:41,052
Where are we going?

5
00:02:41,260 --> 00:02:42,329
Don't you trust me?

6
00:02:43,380 --> 00:02:44,256
No.

7
00:02:44,820 --> 00:02:46,731
I don't trust anybody.

8
00:02:54,340 --> 00:02:56,456
You still haven't said where?

9
00:02:57,260 --> 00:02:59,216
So, what's your name, then?

10
00:02:59,820 --> 00:03:01,014
Betty.

11
00:03:01,540 --> 00:03:03,019
Short for Elizabeth?

12
00:03:03,220 --> 00:03:03,697
Betty.

13
00:03:04,340 --> 00:03:05,409
Where are we going?

14
00:03:05,740 --> 00:03:07,617
To eat. Aren't you hungry?

15
00:03:08,220 --> 00:03:09,653
I'm thirsty.

16
00:03:10,380 --> 00:03:12,098
You can drink too.

17
00:03:14,340 --> 00:03:15,295
You're all gray!

18
00:03:16,980 --> 00:03:18,015
Gray?

19
00:03:18,540 --> 00:03:20,337
Oh, yes, yes. I love gray.

20
00:03:20,980 --> 00:03:25,132
We're going to a place
you don't know. It's very special.

21
00:03:25,420 --> 00:03:27,376
It's near Versailles.

22
00:03:35,300 --> 00:03:36,415
You smoke non-stop.

23
00:03:36,620 --> 00:03:37,939
Non-stop.

24
00:03:38,420 --> 00:03:39,739
2, 3 packs a day?

25
00:03:40,340 --> 00:03:41,250
What do you care?

26
00:03:42,140 --> 00:03:43,937
It's all the same to me.

27
00:03:44,420 --> 00:03:47,378
But I'm a doctor. Didn't I tell you?

28
00:03:48,300 --> 00:03:49,335
Yeah.

29
00:03:49,940 --> 00:03:51,214
Twice already.

30
00:03:54,860 --> 00:03:57,010
Do you like hare?

31
00:03:59,540 --> 00:04:01,895
That's all they serve tonight.

32
00:04:02,140 --> 00:04:04,256
It's cassoulet on Wednesdays.

33
00:04:05,260 --> 00:04:06,773
Is it cassoulet?

34
00:04:07,260 --> 00:04:09,854
Cassoulet... Yes, that's right.

35
00:04:10,060 --> 00:04:12,449
It's cassoulet night.

36
00:04:13,740 --> 00:04:15,253
Takes getting used to.

37
00:04:16,260 --> 00:04:18,012
You either like it or you don't.

38
00:04:19,460 --> 00:04:20,529
Here we are.

39
00:04:36,460 --> 00:04:37,973
Come on.

40
00:04:39,740 --> 00:04:41,617
It doesn't look so hot.

41
00:04:41,820 --> 00:04:43,970
It has it's charm. You'll see.

42
00:04:44,700 --> 00:04:45,849
It's weird...

43
00:04:46,060 --> 00:04:47,095
"The Hole".

44
00:04:47,300 --> 00:04:48,619
Yes, "The Hole".

45
00:04:49,020 --> 00:04:50,339
The Hole.

46
00:04:51,500 --> 00:04:52,933
The Hole.

47
00:04:59,780 --> 00:05:03,739
Funny how they all ingest animals
and never wonder...

48
00:05:03,940 --> 00:05:05,259
How are you, Doc?

49
00:05:06,580 --> 00:05:07,569
You're not listening.

50
00:05:08,700 --> 00:05:10,497
Yes, I am.

51
00:05:10,700 --> 00:05:11,655
What did I say?

52
00:05:12,100 --> 00:05:14,568
That by eating animals people...

53
00:05:15,380 --> 00:05:17,018
Excuse me one moment.

54
00:05:22,940 --> 00:05:24,214
The same?

55
00:05:28,300 --> 00:05:30,336
Your first time in The Hole?

56
00:05:31,660 --> 00:05:32,456
Yeah.

57
00:05:33,060 --> 00:05:34,778
Known Doc long?

58
00:05:35,900 --> 00:05:36,810
No.

59
00:05:38,500 --> 00:05:40,058
Want something to eat?

60
00:05:40,380 --> 00:05:42,052
I'm not hungry, thanks.

61
00:05:43,220 --> 00:05:46,815
Make yourself at home.
Everybody here does.

62
00:06:11,660 --> 00:06:13,696
Sorry to leave you alone.

63
00:06:14,940 --> 00:06:16,498
They served refills.

64
00:06:17,060 --> 00:06:18,334
Well done.

65
00:06:20,140 --> 00:06:21,653
I'm still thirsty.

66
00:06:22,620 --> 00:06:25,339
Joseph! A drink for the lady.

67
00:06:33,260 --> 00:06:34,739
You have an itch?

68
00:06:36,500 --> 00:06:37,569
What?

69
00:06:40,500 --> 00:06:43,173
Here... Right here?

70
00:06:43,980 --> 00:06:46,414
- Yes... I guess.
- Under the skin?

71
00:06:48,740 --> 00:06:49,331
Crawling?

72
00:06:50,180 --> 00:06:51,135
Is what crawling?

73
00:06:51,460 --> 00:06:53,928
Near the surface or deep down?

74
00:06:55,180 --> 00:06:56,613
How does it feel?

75
00:06:58,300 --> 00:06:59,449
They all have

76
00:06:59,660 --> 00:07:00,934
different natures.

77
00:07:01,140 --> 00:07:02,858
What are you talking about?

78
00:07:03,420 --> 00:07:05,695
Worms, my dear child.

79
00:07:06,100 --> 00:07:07,215
What worms?

80
00:07:07,940 --> 00:07:09,737
Don't you know, then?

81
00:07:10,300 --> 00:07:12,768
You have worms under your skin.

82
00:07:13,100 --> 00:07:15,978
All kinds of worms, dear Betty.

83
00:07:16,340 --> 00:07:20,618
Tiny ones, big fat ones,
busy ones, and lazy ones.

84
00:07:21,380 --> 00:07:25,373
