00:54:28,041 --> 00:54:28,632
Don't worry.

792
00:54:28,841 --> 00:54:30,559
That suit's 2 years old.

793
00:54:30,841 --> 00:54:32,752
That's not true, 3 years old.

794
00:54:33,161 --> 00:54:34,150
Here you are.

795
00:54:34,601 --> 00:54:35,511
Thank you.

796
00:54:35,841 --> 00:54:37,911
And another coffee, please.

797
00:54:40,361 --> 00:54:44,149
Well, what should I do with this?

798
00:54:44,561 --> 00:54:46,040
Shall I remove your stain?

799
00:54:46,241 --> 00:54:47,151
Please!

800
00:54:56,801 --> 00:54:58,598
- You're not serious.
- I am!

801
00:54:58,801 --> 00:54:59,870
You're crazy!

802
00:55:00,841 --> 00:55:02,035
Yes!

803
00:55:02,481 --> 00:55:04,119
Yes, I'm crazy!

804
00:55:10,921 --> 00:55:11,433
So...

805
00:55:13,721 --> 00:55:14,710
thought it over?

806
00:55:17,841 --> 00:55:18,990
I'm listening.

807
00:55:21,001 --> 00:55:22,320
Guy, you know...

808
00:55:22,761 --> 00:55:23,989
You don't love me enough?

809
00:55:24,561 --> 00:55:26,597
No, you know that's not true.

810
00:55:27,721 --> 00:55:28,631
So?

811
00:55:29,081 --> 00:55:30,992
I'd rather not get married.

812
00:55:31,401 --> 00:55:32,436
It's better.

813
00:55:32,921 --> 00:55:35,276
Why, if you don't mind telling me?

814
00:55:37,721 --> 00:55:40,997
Because of everything.
Me. My life.

815
00:55:44,601 --> 00:55:46,398
Betty, I wasn't born yesterday.

816
00:55:47,121 --> 00:55:50,431
It's none of my business,
what you've done in the past.

817
00:55:55,481 --> 00:55:57,199
It hasn't been very pretty.

818
00:55:57,841 --> 00:55:58,910
I'm not interested.

819
00:55:59,401 --> 00:56:00,834
You don't understand.

820
00:56:01,881 --> 00:56:03,758
That life... I enjoyed it!

821
00:56:05,841 --> 00:56:07,354
It's gone.

822
00:56:09,481 --> 00:56:11,358
It's gone.

823
00:56:13,241 --> 00:56:14,151
Do you love me?

824
00:56:15,921 --> 00:56:16,910
Yes.

825
00:56:17,281 --> 00:56:19,112
So, life begins here.

826
00:56:19,721 --> 00:56:22,679
It's like we're starting
from scratch,

827
00:56:23,761 --> 00:56:25,274
you and me both.

828
00:56:26,721 --> 00:56:29,440
Saturday we go to Lyon
to meet my mother.

829
00:56:31,321 --> 00:56:34,552
- But Guy, I can't keep house!
- Don't be silly.

830
00:56:34,761 --> 00:56:36,319
We have people for that.

831
00:56:36,761 --> 00:56:38,160
You are my wife.

832
00:56:38,681 --> 00:56:40,876
<i>He is nice, you know.</i>

833
00:56:41,481 --> 00:56:43,597
And he's a good fuck.

834
00:56:44,041 --> 00:56:46,953
That's why sometimes
I think I'm disgusting.

835
00:56:48,121 --> 00:56:50,077
He doesn't take care of me.

836
00:56:50,401 --> 00:56:54,280
He tries, but he only takes care
of what I represent.

837
00:56:54,761 --> 00:56:57,673
Like, if I'm sick,
I'm sent to the doctor.

838
00:56:58,041 --> 00:57:02,000
<i>The family doctor.
And he's something else!</i>

839
00:57:02,441 --> 00:57:05,001
He doesn't want his wife
to be sick.

840
00:57:05,361 --> 00:57:08,558
<i>Oh no. Not me.
The mother of his child.</i>

841
00:57:09,961 --> 00:57:12,316
It's not his fault.
It's his upbringing.

842
00:57:12,601 --> 00:57:14,592
You can't stop yourself, huh?

843
00:57:14,961 --> 00:57:16,917
You're still sublimating.

844
00:57:17,121 --> 00:57:19,635
Hey! You trying to make me fat?

845
00:57:19,841 --> 00:57:22,150
There you are. Typical, that.

846
00:57:22,361 --> 00:57:27,037
<i>You transpose the mental
to the physical. And you accuse me!</i>

847
00:57:27,241 --> 00:57:29,755
That's... that's typical. Careful!

848
00:57:29,961 --> 00:57:33,954
Dr Freud. And I thought you
were studying dermatology.

849
00:57:34,161 --> 00:57:35,514
There's no contradiction.

850
00:57:36,121 --> 00:57:37,839
Humans are a whole:

851
00:57:38,041 --> 00:57:41,716
Exterior and interior,
material and spiritual.

852
00:57:42,241 --> 00:57:43,674
You know your problem?

853
00:57:44,961 --> 00:57:46,440
No. Tell me.

854
00:57:47,481 --> 00:57:51,440
In your tiny little head
you really want to be a heroine.

855
00:57:51,881 --> 00:57:55,396
You have an idea of what
you want to be... should be,

856
00:57:55,601 --> 00:57:58,354
so you fall even deeper.
It's classic!

857
00:57:59,321 --> 00:58:00,993
Me? Fall?

858
00:58:01,921 --> 00:58:05,596
Lying is natural to you.
And not just to others.

859
00:58:05,801 --> 00:58:08,395
You lie to yourself,
afraid of who you are.

860
00:58:08,601 --> 00:58:13,117
<i>Soon as you feel uneasy, pow,
you start telling yourself stories.</i>

861
00:58:14,681 --> 00:58:16,751
Shut up! What am I?

862
00:58:16,961 --> 00:58:19,953
- A guinea pig?
- Okay. Keep it up,

863
00:58:20,161 --> 00:58:22,595
and you'll end up in the morgue...

864
00:58:24,281 --> 00:58:25,236
or the nut house.

865
00:58:30,841 --> 00:58:31,910
Go on. Eat!

866
00:58:33,641 --> 00:58:35,677
I wondered if you were asleep.

867
00:58:38,681 --> 00:58:41,036
Are you all right? Hungry?

868
00:58:43,241 --> 00:58:44,640
Should I order breakfast?

869
00:58:44,841 --> 00:58:46,194
No, thank you.

870
00:58:50,041 --> 00:58:50,757
Not even

871
00:58:50,961 --> 00:58:52,030
a cup of coffee?

872
00:58:55,321 --> 00:58:58,472
Does your pulse rate
sometimes drop sharply?

873
00:59:03,761 --> 00:59:05,240
Do you prefer it dark?

874
00:59:06,441 --> 00:59:07,840
I don't care.

875
00:59:14,241 --> 00:59:16,709
It's depressing, this darkness.

876
00:59:18,321 --> 00:59:21,438
At least you slept.
I didn't hear a peep.

877
00:59:22,601 --> 00:59:24,319
Do you have any pain?

878
00:59:25,281 --> 00:59:26,555
Migraine?

879
00:59:28,001 --> 00:59:32,597
Would you mind if I phoned
a doctor? I know a good one nearby.

880
00:59:33,601 --> 00:59:34,636
Bernard?

881
00:59:35,561 --> 00:59:40,191
No no no. And I promise he won't
ask any indiscreet questions.

882
00:59:40,601 --> 00:59:42,080
I don't care.

883
00:59:42,681 --> 00:59:45,195
Would you like your face washed?

884
00:59:45,721 --> 00:59:47,393
No... no.

885
01:00:01,441 --> 01:00:04,831
Blanche? Laure Levaucher.
Is the doctor in?

886
01:00:06,361 --> 01:00:09,637
Hello, Doctor?
Sorry to bother you.

887
01:00:10,041 --> 01:00:14,239
No, no. I'm calling for a friend
who's staying with me.

888
01:00:14,441 --> 01:00:16,716
<i>I'd like you to come see her.</i>

889
01:00:18,481 --> 01:00:20,676
<i>Well, it's hard to explain...</i>

890
01:00:21,681 --> 01:00:24,036
<i>Last night I gave her
some phenobarbital.</i>

891
01:00:24,241 --> 01:00:26,391
<i>Now her pulse is 53.</i>

892
01:00:27,401 --> 01:00:30,234
<i>No, I don't think it's a reaction.</i>

893
01:00:31,601 --> 01:00:33,592
<i>Oh, 27, 28 years old, I'd say.</i>

894
01:00:33,841 --> 01:00:37,231
<i>Thank you Doctor.
Yes, I'll wait here.</i>

895
01:00:37,521 --> 01:00:39,512
<i>Come directly up to my room.</i>

896
01:01:33,241 --> 01:01:35,550
Betty! You're still asleep?

897
01:01:36,001 --> 01:01:37,593
It's already one o'clock.

898
01:01:38,201 --> 01:01:41,113
The doctor's coming
at quarter-to-two.

899
01:01:41,601 --> 01:01:44,559
How about a wash
or something to eat?

900
01:01:45,241 --> 01:01:46,879
No, thank you, Laure.

901
01:01:47,801 --> 01:01:50,759
Be nice,
and shut the door behind you.

902
01:01:52,601 --> 01:01:54,239
Sure, if you like.

903
01:01:54,961 --> 01:01:56,553
Sleep well.

904
01:02:05,681 --> 01:02:07,512
What are you thinking about?

905
01:02:07,721 --> 01:02:08,676
About you.

906
01:02:09,961 --> 01:02:12,270
- And?
- And what?

907
01:02:12,881 --> 01:02:15,190
And, what do you think about me?

908
01:02:20,441 --> 01:02:21,430
It's very complex.

909
01:02:26,921 --> 01:02:28,115
You're like my sister.

910
01:02:28,801 --> 01:02:29,870
What?

911
01:02:31,241 --> 01:02:33,471
When you preach at me.

912
01:02:38,281 --> 01:02:40,841
When you bug me, I think of her.

913
01:02:42,001 --> 01:02:44,390
What'd you do if I didn't come here?

914
01:02:45,441 --> 01:02:46,794
But you do come here.

915
01:02:47,001 --> 01:02:49,037
- I'd look for you!
- At my place?

916
01:02:49,241 --> 01:02:50,151
Well, yeah.

917
01:02:52,121 --> 01:02:53,315
And my husband?

918
01:03:04,001 --> 01:03:05,434
Betty, my dear,

919
01:03:05,641 --> 01:03:08,599
tonight I'm taking Mother
to the theatre.

920
01:03:08,921 --> 01:03:12,516
- Mother?
- Perfect! I adore Anouilh.

921
01:03:12,721 --> 01:03:15,030
My god! It's Elda's day off!

922
01:03:15,401 --> 01:03:19,474
That's all right.
I don't feel like the theatre.

923
01:03:19,681 --> 01:03:21,034
Well, I must go.

924
01:03:27,641 --> 01:03:29,040
See you tonight.

925
01:03:29,401 --> 01:03:32,120
- I've got to go.
- Stay 5 minutes.

926
01:03:32,361 --> 01:03:34,192
- You'll write me a note?
- A note?

927
01:03:34,401 --> 01:03:35,993
A joke, Mother.

928
01:03:37,881 --> 01:03:39,553
When does Elda get back?

929
01:03:41,241 --> 01:03:42,754
Not before midnight.

930
01:03:44,121 --> 01:03:46,510
The baby looks pale.

931
01:03:47,001 --> 01:03:48,320
We'll look after her.

932
01:03:48,521 --> 01:03:49,874
Won't we, Elizabeth?

933
01:03:50,441 --> 01:03:51,669
Of course, Mother.

934
01:03:52,761 --> 01:03:56,800
After my dentist appointment
I can pick the kids up

935
01:03:57,001 --> 01:03:57,717
at school.

936
01:03:57,921 --> 01:03:59,115
Fine.

937
01:04:04,361 --> 01:04:05,635
See you tonight.

938
01:04:23,801 --> 01:04:25,280
Betty!

939
01:04:25,481 --> 01:04:28,678
Can you go see?
I think I heard crying.

940
01:04:30,441 --> 01:04:31,874
Yes, Mother.

941
01:04:35,121 --> 01:04:37,271
Don't get up, I'm going.

942
01:04:45,721 --> 01:04:46,915
<i>How was the dentist?</i>

943
01:04:48,681 --> 01:04:52,435
The same. You wait an hour,
and then he finds something wrong.

944
01:04:52,641 --> 01:04:54,632
Somehow, he always hurts you.

945
01:04:54,961 --> 01:04:56,155
I'm forever there.

946
01:04:56,361 --> 01:04:59,876
- After 10 years it hurts less.
- That reminds me,

947
01:05:00,081 --> 01:05:01,560
I have to make a call.

948
01:05:02,881 --> 01:05:06,351
I'll take the kids out
to give Granny some peace.

949
01:05:06,841 --> 01:05:08,240
They don't bother me!

950
01:05:08,441 --> 01:05:10,875
That's kind,
but it's better for them.

951
01:05:11,281 --> 01:05:14,273
Remember, Betty.
Dinner at our place!

952
01:05:14,881 --> 01:05:16,314
Of course!

953
01:05:17,081 --> 01:05:19,515
I can't talk. There are people here.

954
01:05:19,721 --> 01:05:23,999
I can't get out.
I'll call after dinner. Around nine.

955
01:05:39,361 --> 01:05:40,714
You won't be lonely?

956
01:05:40,921 --> 01:05:42,877
Don't be silly.

957
01:05:43,921 --> 01:05:45,115
Odile's just upstairs...

958
01:05:46,001 --> 01:05:48,879
Some company!
Hurry, you'll be late.

959
01:05:49,081 --> 01:05:50,036
The tickets, dear?

960
01:05:50,241 --> 01:05:51,879
I've got them, Mother.

961
01:06:00,681 --> 01:06:01,909
You can go. I'm fine.

962
01:06:02,121 --> 01:06:03,474
I can wait Madame.

963
01:06:03,681 --> 01:06:05,194
No, go on. Get some rest.

964
01:06:05,401 --> 01:06:06,914
Thank you. Good night.

965
01:06:23,401 --> 01:06:25,437
Hello! Hello! Is that you?

966
01:06:28,801 --> 01:06:30,200
Are you sad?

967
01:06:31,321 --> 01:06:34,518
Not that! If you knew
what I've been through!

968
01:06:34,761 --> 01:06:36,399
Think I've been laughing?

969
01:06:36,601 --> 01:06:37,795
<i>Did you miss me?</i>

970
01:06:38,601 --> 01:06:40,592
Listen. You know where I live.

971
01:06:41,001 --> 01:06:42,559
The kids are asleep.

972
01:06:42,761 --> 01:06:46,390
The nurse and maid are out,
my husband's at the theatre.

973
01:06:46,601 --> 01:06:47,716
<i>So?</i>

974
01:06:48,401 --> 01:06:49,880
Don't you understand?

975
01:06:51,361 --> 01:06:51,998
Yes.

976
01:06:52,601 --> 01:06:54,159
You don't seem thrilled.

977
01:06:54,761 --> 01:06:56,080
<i>Listen to me,</i>

978
01:06:56,361 --> 01:07:00,320
I've wanted this too long.
You'll see when you get here.

979
01:07:00,641 --> 01:07:01,756
Come.

980
01:07:02,561 --> 01:07:03,596
Okay.

981
01:07:08,281 --> 01:07:09,236
Come.

982
01:07:19,401 --> 01:07:21,312
- Are you afraid?
- No.

983
01:07:23,321 --> 01:07:25,198
Not happy to see where I live?

984
01:07:27,681 --> 01:07:28,716
You don't like it?

985
01:07:28,921 --> 01:07:29,956
Yes, yes.

986
01:07:33,001 --> 01:07:34,480
Well, I hate it.

987
01:07:34,761 --> 01:07:36,035
Come by me.

988
01:07:39,081 --> 01:07:40,799
What's wrong? What is it?

989
01:07:49,841 --> 01:07:53,629
- What about the kids?
- Their room's behind that door.

990
01:07:53,841 --> 01:07:55,035
Wait!

991
01:08:01,961 --> 01:08:04,839
There. If Charlotte wakes,
we'll hear.

992
01:08:15,201 --> 01:08:17,635
Don't be such a lump!

993
01:08:18,801 --> 01:08:20,678
We're going to enjoy this.

994
01:08:28,161 --> 01:08:31,312
I'll get Frédéric.
You lie down on the couch.

995
01:08:48,561 --> 01:08:50,313
No, no. Not on that!

996
01:08:57,361 --> 01:09:01,479
Hurry! My drops... my drops.
Give me 20 drops.

997
01:09:20,561 --> 01:09:23,200
Elizabeth! Guy wants to see you.

998
01:09:35,761 --> 01:09:38,116
In the salon. They want to see you.

999
01:09:40,081 --> 01:09:41,116
Come here.

1000
01:09:56,121 --> 01:09:57,520
You can sit down.

1001
01:10:06,001 --> 01:10:10,950
The counsellor has rushed over
to help me resolve this.

1002
01:10:11,361 --> 01:10:13,113
I know we were wrong,

1003
01:10:13,321 --> 01:10:16,757
Mother and I,
to return without warning,

1004
01:10:17,201 --> 01:10:19,476
but she was unwell.
You'll excuse us?

1005
01:10:19,841 --> 01:10:20,717
Guy!

1006
01:10:23,761 --> 01:10:27,436
Write what the counsellor dictates.
I find it equitable.

1007
01:10:28,321 --> 01:10:30,073
Generous, in fact.

1008
01:10:31,241 --> 01:10:32,799
It's very simple:

1009
01:10:34,521 --> 01:10:36,193
You recognize your wrongs,

1010
01:10:38,881 --> 01:10:41,554
you renounce guardianship
of the children

1011
01:10:42,521 --> 01:10:44,637
as well as the right to see them.

1012
01:10:45,881 --> 01:10:48,953
In exchange, we guarantee,
financially speaking,

1013
01:10:49,441 --> 01:10:52,274
you won't be in any need.

1014
01:10:56,361 --> 01:10:57,840
Either accept

1015
01:10:58,241 --> 01:10:59,913
and all will be well,

1016
01:11:01,201 --> 01:11:02,953
or refuse, and it's war.

1017
01:11:03,161 --> 01:11:05,959
And it's a war you will never win.

1018
01:11:09,881 --> 01:11:11,360
What is it I have to do?

1019
01:11:14,961 --> 01:11:15,916
You write:

1020
01:11:16,121 --> 01:11:17,952
I, the undersigned,

1021
01:11:20,961 --> 01:11:22,679
Elizabeth Etamble...

1022
01:11:22,881 --> 01:11:24,075
<i>She wrote Betty.</i>

1023
01:11:24,281 --> 01:11:26,875
Ah, no. Not Betty! Elizabeth.

1024
01:11:37,041 --> 01:11:40,511
I, the undersigned,
Elizabeth Etamble

1025
01:11:41,961 --> 01:11:43,440
née Fayet,

1026
01:11:44,801 --> 01:11:46,951
28 years old, without profession,

1027
01:11:49,481 --> 01:11:52,279
residing at 6 Ave Ruysdaël, Paris,

1028
01:11:54,441 --> 01:11:57,399
do hereby state

1029
01:11:58,441 --> 01:12:02,559
that I accept without reservation
the conditions...

1030
01:12:06,521 --> 01:12:08,876
A check for your immediate needs.

1031
01:12:10,081 --> 01:12:11,992
When I have your address

1032
01:12:12,201 --> 01:12:15,591
I'll send your affairs
and my lawyer will contact you.

1033
01:12:24,601 --> 01:12:26,637
No, Betty. Please.

1034
01:12:28,281 --> 01:12:30,192
They're asleep.
They wouldn't understand.

1035
01:12:47,921 --> 01:12:49,274
<i>So, you're not well?</i>

1036
01:12:49,841 --> 01:12:53,072
What's the problem?
Well, we'll have a look.

1037
01:12:53,281 --> 01:12:55,351
May I? I'll wash my hands.

1038
01:13:00,481 --> 01:13:03,473
What has she had this morning?
Breakfast?

1039
01:13:03,961 --> 01:13:05,553
No, she wouldn't eat.

1040
01:13:05,761 --> 01:13:07,399
Not even coffee?

1041
01:13:07,601 --> 01:13:08,317
No.

1042
01:13:10,121 --> 01:13:11,713
Are you in much pain?

1043
01:13:12,841 --> 01:13:14,433
No pain anywhere?

1044
01:13:14,641 --> 01:13:17,474
No migraine, chest contractions?

1045
01:13:18,001 --> 01:13:19,229
You can stay if you like.

1046
01:13:19,441 --> 01:13:22,080
- It's all right.
- No. I have a call to make.

1047
01:13:30,441 --> 01:13:33,513
Is that you?
No, I'm at the hotel with Betty.

1048
01:13:33,721 --> 01:13:35,313
The doctor's examining her.

1049
01:13:35,521 --> 01:13:36,840
It's not serious.

1050
01:13:37,721 --> 01:13:39,552
Any drops in blood pressure?

1051
01:13:40,321 --> 01:13:42,118
No... Make it two hours.

1052
01:13:43,281 --> 01:13:44,191
Fine. I'll explain.

1053
01:13:44,481 --> 01:13:45,914
Right... See you later.

1054
01:13:46,321 --> 01:13:47,549
Love you.

1055
01:13:50,481 --> 01:13:51,880
Turn over.

1056
01:13:59,641 --> 01:14:01,154
Any dizzy spells?

1057
01:14:01,361 --> 01:14:03,431
I've had a few recently.

1058
01:14:03,881 --> 01:14:06,634
Serious enough to lose your balance?

1059
01:14:06,841 --> 01:14:08,718
No, not quite...

1060
01:14:11,201 --> 01:14:12,998
Any recent emotional shock?

1061
01:14:13,201 --> 01:14:14,270
Doctor.

1062
01:14:17,321 --> 01:14:21,837
We haven't behaved ourselves.
We've been drinking quite a bit.

1063
01:14:22,881 --> 01:14:27,557
I gave her 2 phenobarbitals
of 100 mgs and she slept calmly.

1064
01:14:27,761 --> 01:14:31,640
The phone woke her up.
She's been like this since then.

1065
01:14:34,281 --> 01:14:36,795
There's nothing wrong organically.

1066
01:14:37,441 --> 01:14:40,478
What you need is quiet
and complete rest.

1067
01:14:40,681 --> 01:14:43,912
- A clinic would be best.
- No. Not that!

1068
01:14:44,121 --> 01:14:46,715
I won't insist.

1069
01:14:46,961 --> 01:14:50,112
If you behave,
the hotel is as good as anywhere.

1070
01:14:50,601 --> 01:14:51,511
Do you have guests?

1071
01:14:51,721 --> 01:14:53,120
No, no one.

1072
01:14:53,321 --> 01:14:54,993
Fine. That's best.

1073
01:14:55,561 --> 01:14:59,349
All right. No going out
for 4 or 5 days. Don't eat,

1074
01:14:59,561 --> 01:15:02,633
except at night,
a light vegetable soup.

1075
01:15:02,841 --> 01:15:05,116
Peace and quiet. Understand?

1076
01:15:06,161 --> 01:15:07,037
Yes.

1077
01:15:07,361 --> 01:15:08,237
Good.

1078
01:15:08,561 --> 01:15:10,074
Now, turn over.

1079
01:15:11,481 --> 01:15:13,517
I'm giving you a shot.

1080
01:15:23,401 --> 01:15:24,675
No, Betty. Please.

1081
01:15:26,001 --> 01:15:27,878
They're asleep.
They wouldn't understand.

1082
01:15:38,561 --> 01:15:41,439
- Ice?
- Yeah. Make it a double.

1083
01:15:45,081 --> 01:15:46,400
With soda?

1084
01:15:47,001 --> 01:15:48,798
I don't care... No.

1085
01:15:52,641 --> 01:15:54,074
Give me another.

1086
01:16:17,481 --> 01:16:18,072
Don't bother.

1087
01:16:18,281 --> 01:16:20,351
- He's not there.
- He's not back?

1088
01:16:20,721 --> 01:16:21,676
He came back and left.

1089
01:16:22,361 --> 01:16:26,912
With his bag and his instrument,
like he was in a rush.

1090
01:16:27,441 --> 01:16:29,477
And he said to rent the studio.

1091
01:17:01,721 --> 01:17:03,473
Isn't Philippe here?

1092
01:17:03,881 --> 01:17:05,360
Philippe? The saxophone?

1093
01:17:05,561 --> 01:17:06,357
Yeah.

1094
01:17:14,881 --> 01:17:18,191
I don't see him.
He must have got a replacement.

1095
01:17:20,561 --> 01:17:21,914
Buy you a drink?

1096
01:17:23,281 --> 01:17:24,600
- If you like.
- I'd like to.

1097
01:17:24,801 --> 01:17:25,756
What'll it be?

1098
01:17:25,961 --> 01:17:27,235
A whisky.

1099
01:17:28,201 --> 01:17:31,637
A whisky. Cloclo, a double whisky
for the lovely lady.

1100
01:17:32,961 --> 01:17:33,598
Ice?

1101
01:17:34,481 --> 01:17:35,436
Yeah.

1102
01:17:37,321 --> 01:17:38,595
Soda?

1103
01:17:39,361 --> 01:17:40,840
I don't care...

1104
01:17:41,201 --> 01:17:42,077
No.

1105
01:17:43,361 --> 01:17:45,113
What's your name, my beauty?

1106
01:17:45,521 --> 01:17:46,078
Betty.

1107
01:17:48,001 --> 01:17:49,195
It's over there!

1108
01:17:54,361 --> 01:17:55,794
Through here!

1109
01:18:04,721 --> 01:18:05,915
Is Number 3 free, Maria?

1110
01:18:06,121 --> 01:18:07,793
Right away, Madame.

1111
01:18:08,161 --> 01:18:09,594
Go ahead!

1112
01:18:32,841 --> 01:18:34,069
Strip off!

1113
01:18:37,361 --> 01:18:38,840
On your feet, my girl.

1114
01:18:39,241 --> 01:18:40,754
Cut the shit. The hour's over.

1115
01:18:41,481 --> 01:18:42,755
I want to sleep. Sleep.

1116
01:18:42,961 --> 01:18:44,474
But not here.

1117
01:18:44,721 --> 01:18:47,189
Move it or Mr Charles'll take over.

1118
01:18:47,641 --> 01:18:51,429
Don't want to leave?
I'll kick your ass outta here!

1119
01:18:51,641 --> 01:18:55,270
I bet your papers aren't right.
And I don't like that!

1120
01:18:55,481 --> 01:18:56,630
Move it!

1121
01:18:57,841 --> 01:18:59,752
Take your things with you!
I need the room!

1122
01:19:01,761 --> 01:19:04,036
Just what we need to get hassled!

1123
01:19:22,121 --> 01:19:25,318
He's just a poor kid, see,
and he was terrified.

1124
01:19:25,521 --> 01:19:28,399
If I don't find him
he won't come back.

1125
01:19:29,001 --> 01:19:30,195
He's scared of Guy.

1126
01:19:31,441 --> 01:19:34,672
Guy? He doesn't give a shit!
You know what?

1127
01:19:35,121 --> 01:19:36,952
I'm sure he knew all along!

1128
01:19:37,681 --> 01:19:38,716
You all right? Happy?

1129
01:19:43,121 --> 01:19:44,918
Where you taking me?

1130
01:19:45,961 --> 01:19:47,474
<i>You're not taking me?</i>

1131
01:19:47,681 --> 01:19:50,115
Me? Where you want me
to take you?

1132
01:19:51,521 --> 01:19:53,193
You don't know where to go?

1133
01:19:54,641 --> 01:19:55,596
No.

1134
01:19:56,761 --> 01:19:58,831
You're not a thief, are you?

1135
01:20:01,241 --> 01:20:02,993
How about my place?

1136
01:20:04,121 --> 01:20:06,032
We could go to my place, huh?

1137
01:21:13,761 --> 01:21:15,638
Quiet. I think she's asleep.

1138
01:21:15,841 --> 01:21:18,719
No, wait. I want to make sure.

1139
01:22:08,121 --> 01:22:09,634
What else did she say?

1140
01:22:09,841 --> 01:22:12,150
So much I can't remember it all.

1141
01:22:12,841 --> 01:22:14,513
She's a poor lost soul.

1142
01:22:14,721 --> 01:22:18,430
She'll spend her life looking,
not knowing what for.

1143
01:22:18,641 --> 01:22:20,199
There are times

1144
01:22:20,521 --> 01:22:22,477
she looks like a stray dog.

1145
01:22:25,521 --> 01:22:27,751
But sometimes her eyes...

1146
01:22:28,561 --> 01:22:31,155
are completely blank.
There's no expression.

1147
01:22:32,041 --> 01:22:35,556
- Do you think she's cold?
- No, the poor thing.

1148
01:22:39,001 --> 01:22:40,036
Maybe she'll wind up

1149
01:22:40,241 --> 01:22:44,439
getting adopted like a stray dog
by a Good Samaritan.

1150
01:23:46,081 --> 01:23:47,309
So, is she asleep?

1151
01:23:48,281 --> 01:23:49,191
So it seems.

1152
01:23:50,281 --> 01:23:52,237
You see? What did I tell you?

1153
01:23:52,761 --> 01:23:54,274
Give me a drink.

1154
01:24:17,801 --> 01:24:20,759
Don't bother, angel, I'll get it.

1155
01:24:23,601 --> 01:24:25,796
No, this is Laure Levaucher.

1156
01:24:30,201 --> 01:24:33,034
A Mr. Etamble
wants to speak to you.

1157
01:24:33,241 --> 01:24:36,233
It might be Frédéric.
Ask his first name.

1158
01:24:36,441 --> 01:24:38,432
That's not so easy.

1159
01:24:39,521 --> 01:24:41,910
Which Mr. Etamble, may I ask?

1160
01:24:43,841 --> 01:24:44,751
Your husband.

1161
01:24:46,361 --> 01:24:50,559
- Should he come up?
- No, no! I don't want him up here!

1162
01:24:50,761 --> 01:24:52,877
Tell him I'm coming down.

1163
01:24:53,081 --> 01:24:54,275
But the doctor said...

1164
01:24:54,481 --> 01:24:57,917
I don't want him here.
Anyway, I feel all right.

1165
01:24:58,121 --> 01:25:02,080
No, tell him I'll meet him
downstairs in half an hour.

1166
01:25:20,681 --> 01:25:22,080
Am I disturbing you?

1167
01:25:23,881 --> 01:25:25,439
No, of course not.

1168
01:25:25,641 --> 01:25:29,111
Florent hardly recognized
your voice on the phone.

1169
01:25:29,881 --> 01:25:32,759
I was afraid
you were sick or something.

1170
01:25:32,961 --> 01:25:36,510
I was tired, that's all.
I'm better now.

1171
01:25:36,721 --> 01:25:38,439
Have you seen a doctor?

1172
01:25:38,761 --> 01:25:39,876
What did he say?

1173
01:25:40,081 --> 01:25:42,151
I'll be okay in 3 or 4 days.

1174
01:25:42,481 --> 01:25:44,437
Can't we go outside?

1175
01:25:44,681 --> 01:25:46,433
Is someone looking after you?

1176
01:25:46,921 --> 01:25:48,070
<i>A girl friend.</i>

1177
01:25:59,161 --> 01:26:00,071
Are the kids well?

1178
01:26:00,281 --> 01:26:02,954
Yes, but Charlotte has a cold

1179
01:26:03,161 --> 01:26:05,470
and she's furious
about being kept in.

1180
01:26:10,001 --> 01:26:11,639
Is your mother back in Lyon?

1181
01:26:12,401 --> 01:26:13,595
Tomorrow.

1182
01:26:19,481 --> 01:26:21,039
I wanted to talk about

1183
01:26:22,481 --> 01:26:23,675
the paper you signed.

1184
01:26:23,881 --> 01:26:25,030
I...

1185
01:26:26,241 --> 01:26:27,959
I don't intend
to use it right away.

1186
01:26:28,921 --> 01:26:32,994
I was really worried
about not having heard from you.

1187
01:26:33,441 --> 01:26:35,238
That's what Florent told me.

1188
01:26:35,641 --> 01:26:39,316
I asked him to call
and arrange to meet you.

1189
01:26:39,881 --> 01:26:41,678
But you refused, so...

1190
01:26:42,321 --> 01:26:43,959
I wanted to get better first.

1191
01:26:46,641 --> 01:26:47,756
Had a breakdown?

1192
01:26:47,961 --> 01:26:50,714
I don't know.
Anyway, it's not serious.

1193
01:26:53,321 --> 01:26:54,117
Well, look...

1194
01:26:54,321 --> 01:26:58,200
In a situation like this,
we can't rush things.

1195
01:26:58,401 --> 01:27:02,076
We have to think this out carefully.

1196
01:27:02,401 --> 01:27:04,119
We're not alone in this.

1197
01:27:05,681 --> 01:27:07,478
We debated it a long time,

1198
01:27:08,241 --> 01:27:12,314
Mother, Frédéric and I.
You may not think it's the best way.

1199
01:27:12,801 --> 01:27:15,759
But you can see that it would

1200
01:27:16,081 --> 01:27:19,960
be difficult for you
to come home right away.

1201
01:27:20,601 --> 01:27:24,150
But you can't stay alone.
You are alone here?

1202
01:27:24,401 --> 01:27:28,519
- Weren't you told at the desk?
- No... yes. I knew.

1203
01:27:30,201 --> 01:27:34,399
We thought as an experiment,
you might go with Mother to Lyon.

1204
01:27:34,601 --> 01:27:38,560
But you can stay here
a little longer. There's no rush.

1205
01:27:39,681 --> 01:27:42,036
You can live with her a while.

1206
01:27:43,641 --> 01:27:46,280
And then, later on...

1207
01:27:47,161 --> 01:27:48,753
Was this your idea?

1208
01:27:50,081 --> 01:27:52,720
We all... discussed it.

1209
01:27:55,801 --> 01:27:57,757
You... thought I'd accept?

1210
01:27:57,961 --> 01:27:59,314
I don't know.

1211
01:27:59,641 --> 01:28:01,120
I don't know now.

1212
01:28:02,041 --> 01:28:03,110
You want that?

1213
01:28:03,321 --> 01:28:04,913
I'm thinking of the children.

1214
01:28:06,321 --> 01:28:08,039
And I'm thinking of you too.

1215
01:28:08,281 --> 01:28:13,116
Thank you, Guy. I'm really touched
by your gesture, really I am.

1216
01:28:13,321 --> 01:28:17,200
The same goes for your mother.
Thank her for me.

1217
01:28:20,121 --> 01:28:21,315
Then it's no?

1218
01:28:21,641 --> 01:28:22,960
It's better this way.

1219
01:28:23,161 --> 01:28:25,880
Not so much for me
as for all of you.

1220
01:28:26,601 --> 01:28:29,479
I warned you. Remember?

1221
01:28:30,721 --> 01:28:32,837
But you wouldn't listen.

1222
01:28:35,161 --> 01:28:37,277
But I'm glad you came.

1223
01:28:37,641 --> 01:28:40,280
It's better to part this way.

1224
01:28:41,001 --> 01:28:42,400
Hey kid, you getting romantic?

1225
01:28:46,441 --> 01:28:48,716
I'll call Florent in a few days.

1226
01:28:49,281 --> 01:28:50,999
Get going, now.

1227
01:28:52,521 --> 01:28:54,512
And don't forget
to thank your mother.

1228
01:28:57,601 --> 01:29:00,161
It's not my fault if I hurt you.

1229
01:29:01,001 --> 01:29:03,276
But I'm asking you to forgive me.

1230
01:29:03,841 --> 01:29:04,512
Get going, now.

1231
01:29:04,721 --> 01:29:06,518
- Are you sure?
- Yes.

1232
01:29:06,921 --> 01:29:07,831
Go on.

1233
01:29:10,121 --> 01:29:11,713
You don't need anything?

1234
01:29:12,281 --> 01:29:13,999
No, nothing at all.

1235
01:29:15,561 --> 01:29:17,392
Good luck, Betty.

1236
01:29:17,601 --> 01:29:18,829
Thanks.

1237
01:29:19,601 --> 01:29:21,432
You too, Guy.

1238
01:29:38,601 --> 01:29:39,829
Thanks.

1239
01:29:52,201 --> 01:29:53,316
So, how'd it go?

1240
01:29:53,521 --> 01:29:54,715
Just fine.

1241
01:29:55,081 --> 01:29:56,400
He asked me back.

1242
01:29:56,601 --> 01:29:57,636
Oh, really?

1243
01:29:59,121 --> 01:30:00,076
And what did you say?

1244
01:30:00,281 --> 01:30:01,555
I said no.

1245
01:30:03,641 --> 01:30:04,676
It's over.

1246
01:30:04,881 --> 01:30:05,996
Feel up to it?

1247
01:30:07,681 --> 01:30:09,956
Oh, yes. Can I have a cigarette?

1248
01:30:19,881 --> 01:30:21,951
Can I leave you?
I have things to do.

1249
01:30:22,161 --> 01:30:23,230
And you're okay now.

1250
01:30:23,481 --> 01:30:25,358
Don't worry.

1251
01:30:25,561 --> 01:30:27,756
Anyway, you've played
the nursemaid long enough.

1252
01:30:27,961 --> 01:30:28,916
No, not at all.

1253
01:30:29,121 --> 01:30:30,315
Going to The Hole?

1254
01:30:30,521 --> 01:30:34,833
No, Paris. I'm seeing my banker
and accountant.

1255
01:30:35,041 --> 01:30:36,952
Lots of very exciting people.

1256
01:30:37,881 --> 01:30:39,314
Well, I'll be running along.

1257
01:30:39,641 --> 01:30:41,518
If there's a problem, call Mario.

1258
01:30:42,761 --> 01:30:44,194
See you tonight.

1259
01:30:45,801 --> 01:30:46,756
Try to rest.

1260
01:30:48,361 --> 01:30:49,680
Goodbye, Laure.

1261
01:31:31,481 --> 01:31:32,596
Mario.

1262
01:31:35,521 --> 01:31:37,751
It's you. You're here.

1263
01:31:38,001 --> 01:31:39,229
Ah, it's so good.

1264
01:32:29,561 --> 01:32:30,789
Afraid?

1265
01:32:31,801 --> 01:32:32,597
No.

1266
01:32:42,321 --> 01:32:43,993
I have to go to The Hole.

1267
01:32:44,201 --> 01:32:45,520
I'm coming along.

1268
01:32:46,521 --> 01:32:48,830
No way: The doc said...

1269
01:32:50,601 --> 01:32:53,115
He doesn't know
what it is to be a woman.

1270
01:33:04,041 --> 01:33:06,271
I've never been happier. And you?

1271
01:33:06,481 --> 01:33:07,550
I'm happy.

1272
01:33:51,081 --> 01:33:53,231
- Where do you live?
- Over the club.

1273
01:33:53,441 --> 01:33:55,113
It's an old farm.

1274
01:33:55,321 --> 01:33:56,720
It's all beams.

1275
01:34:04,801 --> 01:34:07,235
We'll have champagne tonight.

1276
01:34:08,441 --> 01:34:09,590
Okay?

1277
01:34:10,441 --> 01:34:13,035
And I won't drink too much.
I promise.

1278
01:35:09,761 --> 01:35:13,515
Have my bill sent to Lyon.
You have the address?

1279
01:35:13,721 --> 01:35:18,112
No problem, Madame.
We hope to see you again soon.

1280
01:35:18,841 --> 01:35:19,876
Goodbye, François.

1281
01:35:20,081 --> 01:35:21,799
Goodbye, Madame. Thank you.

1282
01:35:52,921 --> 01:35:54,400
<i>LYON</i>

1283
01:36:04,241 --> 01:36:05,515
Remember Madame Levaucher?

1284
01:36:07,801 --> 01:36:09,519
Laure Levaucher?

1285
01:36:09,921 --> 01:36:11,115
The Professor's widow?

1286
01:36:11,321 --> 01:36:13,710
Yes. She just died.

1287
01:36:14,201 --> 01:36:16,192
Her maid
found her dead in bed.

1288
01:36:16,521 --> 01:36:17,749
It's in the paper.

1289
01:36:19,921 --> 01:36:22,276
Didn't she leave Lyon
a long time ago?

1290
01:36:23,361 --> 01:36:24,510
To live in Paris?

1291
01:36:24,801 --> 01:36:29,829
Versailles. But she kept
her apartment here for visits.

1292
01:36:31,201 --> 01:36:32,156
Was she sick?

1293
01:36:33,041 --> 01:36:34,156
They didn't say.

1294
01:36:36,081 --> 01:36:38,037
She wasn't all that old.

1295
01:36:39,161 --> 01:36:40,071
Forty-nine.

1296
01:36:41,401 --> 01:36:42,914
That's not old!

1297
01:36:44,961 --> 01:36:46,997
How are your children?

1298
01:36:48,201 --> 01:36:51,398
Just fine. Very happy.

1299
01:36:51,961 --> 01:36:54,270
Guy's children are adorable.

1300
01:36:54,841 --> 01:36:57,196
But that poor Laure Levaucher.

1301
01:36:57,401 --> 01:37:01,076
I used to run into her
from time to time.

1302
01:37:02,201 --> 01:37:05,591
A beautiful woman,
always rather pale.

1303
01:37:06,561 --> 01:37:08,552
But I never thought she was sick.

1304
01:37:16,041 --> 01:37:20,637
<i>She could never have known
that Laure had died</i>

1305
01:37:20,841 --> 01:37:24,151
<i>because Betty had survived.
It was one or the other...</i>

1306
01:37:24,361 --> 01:37:26,113
<i>And Betty had won.</i>

1307
01:39:15,241 --> 01:39:18,392
Subtitles:
Lenny Borger - David Aronson

1308
01:39:18,601 --> 01:39:20,717
Subtitling: C.M.C. - Paris

1309
